      • getId

        public long getId()
        Description copied from interface: EnvironmentAgent
        The id of the environment agent, which must be unique. That is, the NSM requires that two agents never have the same id, since the norm synthesis cycle may not work correctly
        Specified by:
        getId in interface EnvironmentAgent
        Returns:
        a long number, which is the id of the environment agent
